Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer I* role with *Progress Software*. I bring over three years of professional experience in backend and systems-level software development, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my engineering roles, I have built and maintained production-grade backend systems that directly reflect the platform development discipline and code quality standards the OpenEdge Core Platform team demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I applied OOP principles and secure development practices to implement features for a platform interaction layer spanning 1,000+ endpoints — the same kind of well-scoped feature work central to this role. I built and maintained unit tests, functional tests, and integration tests to enforce code quality across complex execution paths, and refactored prompt-routing and caching systems, reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and API costs by 50%. I also routinely leveraged AI-assisted development tools (Codex, Claude Code) to accelerate delivery while applying engineering judgment to validate generated code for correctness and security — directly mirroring Progress Software's guidelines for responsible AI use in development workflows. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I contributed to backend systems supporting thousands of users: building a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis with secure OOP design patterns, and participating in code reviews and agile sprint ceremonies across a 30+ application platform. I also refactored long-running data import workflows using AWS Step Functions, improving maintainability — the kind of modernization work the OpenEdge team values.

My academic research and personal projects have given me hands-on exposure to systems-level development and developer tooling. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I developed automated tests and evaluation pipelines for model training workflows on an HPC cluster, and refactored inference pipelines using vLLM for improved maintainability and deployment reliability. My Dark Factory project — an orchestrator for AI coding CLIs written in Rust — demonstrates direct systems-level engineering: implementing PTY-based CLI control, applying secure development by validating every command before execution, and designing an event-driven architecture with real-time distributed state using Y-crdt. These projects reflect the compiler-adjacent, runtime-aware, and developer-tooling interests Progress Software highlights as preferred qualifications for this role.

I have always been passionate about powering software products that enable every business to move with agility, and I envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Progress Software's mission to power AI experiences and infrastructure for organizations of every scale. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

